  <section id="elijah-dajjal">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-tag">¬ß VIII ‚Äî New Hypothesis</span>
      <h2>Is the Dajjal Actually Elijah?</h2>
      <p>A reader proposed this during the debate. It opens a fourth mapping possibility that neither Claude nor Grok had considered ‚Äî and it may be the most explosive connection of all.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>The Hypothesis:</strong> The Islamic Dajjal ‚Äî the one-eyed deceiver who performs miracles, controls rain and crops, and is killed near Jerusalem ‚Äî may be the Biblical prophet Elijah returning in the last days as prophesied in Malachi 4:5, Matthew 17:11, and Revelation 11.
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-family:'Cinzel Decorative',serif;color:var(--gold-light);font-size:16px;margin:40px 0 20px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)">
      The Biblical Case for Elijah's Return
    </h3>

    <div style="overflow-x:auto;margin-bottom:40px">
    <table class="verse-table" style="width:100%">
      <thead><tr><th>Reference</th><th>Content</th><th>Relevance</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="verse-ref">Malachi 4:5</span></td>
          <td>"See, I will send the prophet Elijah to you before that great and dreadful day of the LORD comes."</td>
          <td>Direct prophecy ‚Äî Elijah returns before the end. Not yet fulfilled (John the Baptist was a type, not the literal fulfillment per Matthew 17:11).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="verse-ref">Matthew 17:11</span></td>
          <td>"Jesus replied, 'Elijah is coming and will restore all things.'" ‚Äî Future tense, even after John the Baptist.</td>
          <td>Jesus himself confirms a future literal Elijah. "Restore all things" ‚Äî global scope of mission.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="verse-ref">Revelation 11:3-6</span></td>
          <td>Two Witnesses prophesy 1,260 days (3.5 years). Power to shut up rain, call fire, turn water to blood, strike earth with plagues. Killed in Jerusalem. Resurrected after 3.5 days.</td>
          <td>Universally identified as Elijah (drought/fire) and Moses or Enoch. <strong>Elijah never died</strong> ‚Äî taken in a chariot of fire (2 Kings 2:11). He must die in the end times.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="verse-ref">James 5:17</span></td>
          <td>"Elijah was a human being, even as we are. He prayed earnestly that it would not rain, and it did not rain on the land for <strong>three and a half years</strong>."</td>
          <td>3.5 years ‚Äî exact same timeframe as Tribulation, Two Witnesses' ministry, and Dajjal's reign in various hadith. A deliberate prophetic signature.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="verse-ref">2 Kings 1:10-12</span></td>
          <td>Elijah calls fire from heaven twice, consuming 102 soldiers. This is his most spectacular miracle.</td>
          <td>Revelation 13:13 ‚Äî the False Prophet "performed great signs, even causing fire to come down from heaven." Fire from heaven = Elijah's signature. The False Prophet is an Elijah-imitator.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-family:'Cinzel Decorative',serif;color:#f08c4b;font-size:16px;margin:40px 0 20px;padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)">
      Elijah vs Dajjal ‚Äî Parallel Characteristics
    </h3>

    <div style="overflow-x:auto;margin-bottom:40px">
    <table class="compare-table" style="width:100%">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>CHARACTERISTIC</th>
          <th style="color:#4aab7a">‚úù ELIJAH (Biblical)</th>
          <th style="color:#f08c4b">‚òΩ DAJJAL (Islamic)</th>
          <th>MATCH</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><span class="trait-label">Control over rain/weather</span></td>
